<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="577" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1855,2024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1855,1880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Externally, 
<taxonomicName box="[464,698,1855,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[464,698,1855,1879]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Stigmella serpentina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[709,802,1855,1880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,802,1855,1880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
mostly resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1170,1856,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pangorica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1024,1170,1856,1879]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">S. pangorica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1181,1275,1855,1880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1181,1275,1855,1880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName box="[1286,1436,1856,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentina">
<emphasis box="[1286,1436,1856,1879]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">S. serpentina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[301,449,1892,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pangorica">
<emphasis box="[301,449,1892,1915]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">S. pangorica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as having a dark collar and strong purple iridescence of the forewing. In the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName box="[264,414,1928,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentina">
<emphasis box="[264,414,1928,1951]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">S. serpentina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all known Neotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[838,943,1927,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[838,943,1927,1951]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Stigmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a single and very slender (needle-like) apical process of the valva. 
<taxonomicName box="[478,625,1964,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pangorica">
<emphasis box="[478,625,1964,1987]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">S. pangorica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two apical processes on each valva, and its uncus possesses four caudal lobes instead two as in 
<taxonomicName box="[491,637,2000,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentina">
<emphasis box="[491,637,2000,2023]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">S. serpentina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
