<emphasis bold="true" box="[762,842,1943,1964]" pageId="3" pageNumber="579">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, paratype, slide no. AD704.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[302,405,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,193,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. 7, moth, holotype; 8, 9, same, paratypes; 10, 11, male genitalia, capsule, holotype, slide no. AD 705; 12, same, phallus, paratype, slide no. AD 615; 13, same, holotype, slide no. AD 705." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243314/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 
<quantity box="[622,761,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.6 mm</quantity>
, wingspan 
<quantity box="[889,1029,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="5.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="5.4" valueMax="5.7" valueMin="5.1">5.1–5.7 mm</quantity>
. Collar fuscous to dark bronze with golden gloss, sometimes without purple iridescence; antennae with 
<number box="[934,1004,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="31.0" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="30.0">30–32</number>
segments. Forewing with purple and blue iridescence but usually, in contrast to males, with distinctive postmedian shining golden fascia; a few golden scales can be developed along tornal margin; cilia dark grey-brown to fuscous, with strong golden gloss except on tornus where golden gloss weak or absent. Abdomen dark grey-brown to fuscous and glossy both on upper and underside. Otherwise as males.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,369,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[384,515,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,193,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. 7, moth, holotype; 8, 9, same, paratypes; 10, 11, male genitalia, capsule, holotype, slide no. AD 705; 12, same, phallus, paratype, slide no. AD 615; 13, same, holotype, slide no. AD 705." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243314/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Figs 
<number box="[440,515,368,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Capsule longer (
<number box="[717,760,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="325.0">325</number>
µm) than wide (
<number box="[945,989,368,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="200.0">200</number>
µm). Vinculum usually with very small triangular lateral lobes (
<figureCitation box="[416,499,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,193,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. 7, moth, holotype; 8, 9, same, paratypes; 10, 11, male genitalia, capsule, holotype, slide no. AD 705; 12, same, phallus, paratype, slide no. AD 615; 13, same, holotype, slide no. AD 705." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243314/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[468,499,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); occasionally one of these lobes can be larger than other. Uncus with two triangular caudal lobes (
<figureCitation box="[309,394,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,193,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. 7, moth, holotype; 8, 9, same, paratypes; 10, 11, male genitalia, capsule, holotype, slide no. AD 705; 12, same, phallus, paratype, slide no. AD 615; 13, same, holotype, slide no. AD 705." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243314/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[363,394,440,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gnathos with two large caudal processes and very large central plate (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1349,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,193,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. 7, moth, holotype; 8, 9, same, paratypes; 10, 11, male genitalia, capsule, holotype, slide no. AD 705; 12, same, phallus, paratype, slide no. AD 615; 13, same, holotype, slide no. AD 705." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243314/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Figs 10, 11</figureCitation>
). Valva 
<number box="[151,248,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="227.5" valueMax="230.0" valueMin="225.0">225–230</number>
µm long, broadest at base (
<number box="[568,639,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="80.0" valueMax="85.0" valueMin="75.0">75–85</number>
µm), gradually narrowing towards apex, with single and very slender (needle-like) apical process (
<figureCitation box="[475,557,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,193,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. 7, moth, holotype; 8, 9, same, paratypes; 10, 11, male genitalia, capsule, holotype, slide no. AD 705; 12, same, phallus, paratype, slide no. AD 615; 13, same, holotype, slide no. AD 705." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243314/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[528,557,512,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Transtilla with short transverse bar and short, triangular lateral processes (or angular, without lateral processes). Phallus (
<figureCitation box="[663,798,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,193,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. 7, moth, holotype; 8, 9, same, paratypes; 10, 11, male genitalia, capsule, holotype, slide no. AD 705; 12, same, phallus, paratype, slide no. AD 615; 13, same, holotype, slide no. AD 705." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243314/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Figs 12, 13</figureCitation>
) 
<number box="[817,916,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="230.0" valueMax="235.0" valueMin="225.0">225–235</number>
µm long, 
<number box="[1042,1112,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="82.5" valueMax="85.0" valueMin="80.0">80–85</number>
µm broad; vesica with two spine-like cornuti, one of which slightly shorter than other.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,398,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[415,548,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[161,1433,301,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[153,1433,301,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Female genitalia of Stigmella serpentina sp. nov., paratype, slide no. AD 704." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243315/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Figs 
<number box="[474,548,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="15.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="14.0">14–16</number>
</figureCitation>
). Total length 
<number box="[715,757,620,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="700.0">700</number>
µm. Abdominal tip narrow. Accessory sac small (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1423,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[161,1433,301,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[153,1433,301,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Female genitalia of Stigmella serpentina sp. nov., paratype, slide no. AD 704." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243315/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1423,620,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ductus spermathecae with one coil (
<figureCitation box="[580,668,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[161,1433,301,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[153,1433,301,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Female genitalia of Stigmella serpentina sp. nov., paratype, slide no. AD 704." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243315/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[637,668,655,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). Corpus bursae small (about 
<number box="[1024,1066,656,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="270.0">270</number>
µm excluding folded part) and narrow (about 
<number box="[316,358,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="100.0">100</number>
µm) (
<figureCitation box="[427,510,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[161,1433,301,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[153,1433,301,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Female genitalia of Stigmella serpentina sp. nov., paratype, slide no. AD 704." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243315/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[479,510,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Bionomics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[340,444,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1732,1755]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,248,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1433,193,1711]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Bionomics of the new species. 1, 2, habitat, tropical montane moist forest, Pangor Canyon, 30 km NE Pallatanga, Ecuador, 1 ° 52 ' 41 &quot; S, 78 ° 54 ' 11 &quot; W, elevation 3025 m a. s. l.; 3, Liabum sp. (Asteraceae), a host-plant of Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. and S. pangorica sp. nov.; 4 – 6, leaf-mines of S. serpentina sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243313/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Figs 
<number box="[399,444,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mines in leaves (
<figureCitation box="[662,764,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1732,1755]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,248,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1433,193,1711]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Bionomics of the new species. 1, 2, habitat, tropical montane moist forest, Pangor Canyon, 30 km NE Pallatanga, Ecuador, 1 ° 52 ' 41 &quot; S, 78 ° 54 ' 11 &quot; W, elevation 3025 m a. s. l.; 3, Liabum sp. (Asteraceae), a host-plant of Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. and S. pangorica sp. nov.; 4 – 6, leaf-mines of S. serpentina sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243313/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Figs 
<number box="[721,764,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Adans." authorityName="Adans." box="[813,987,727,752]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Liabum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,898,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Liabum</emphasis>
Adans.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1129,728,752]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) (possibly 
<taxonomicName authority="H. Rob." authorityName="H. Rob." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Liabum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barclayae">
<emphasis box="[1257,1400,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">L. barclayae</emphasis>
H. Rob.
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[230,299,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1732,1755]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,248,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1433,193,1711]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Bionomics of the new species. 1, 2, habitat, tropical montane moist forest, Pangor Canyon, 30 km NE Pallatanga, Ecuador, 1 ° 52 ' 41 &quot; S, 78 ° 54 ' 11 &quot; W, elevation 3025 m a. s. l.; 3, Liabum sp. (Asteraceae), a host-plant of Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. and S. pangorica sp. nov.; 4 – 6, leaf-mines of S. serpentina sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243313/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[283,299,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Egg on upper side of the leaf. Larva pale greenish yellow with pale brown head; mine in February. Mine gallery contorted, with dark brown to black frass almost fully filling width of the gallery (
<figureCitation box="[1226,1329,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1732,1755]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,248,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1433,193,1711]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Bionomics of the new species. 1, 2, habitat, tropical montane moist forest, Pangor Canyon, 30 km NE Pallatanga, Ecuador, 1 ° 52 ' 41 &quot; S, 78 ° 54 ' 11 &quot; W, elevation 3025 m a. s. l.; 3, Liabum sp. (Asteraceae), a host-plant of Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. and S. pangorica sp. nov.; 4 – 6, leaf-mines of S. serpentina sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243313/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
Figs 
<number box="[1283,1329,799,824]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Cocoon beige-brown; length 
<quantity box="[384,521,836,861]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.8 mm</quantity>
, maximal width 
<quantity box="[709,847,836,860]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.4 mm</quantity>
. Adults emerged in March.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="580" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,871,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Distribution</emphasis>
. Known from a single locality in Equatorial Andes (Chimborazo Province, 
<collectingCountry box="[1193,1292,871,896]" name="Ecuador" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
). The habitat is tropical montane moist forest (
<figureCitation box="[520,622,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1732,1755]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,248,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1433,193,1711]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Bionomics of the new species. 1, 2, habitat, tropical montane moist forest, Pangor Canyon, 30 km NE Pallatanga, Ecuador, 1 ° 52 ' 41 &quot; S, 78 ° 54 ' 11 &quot; W, elevation 3025 m a. s. l.; 3, Liabum sp. (Asteraceae), a host-plant of Stigmella serpentina sp. nov. and S. pangorica sp. nov.; 4 – 6, leaf-mines of S. serpentina sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243313/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="580" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,943,968]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[793,911,944,967]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentina">
<emphasis box="[793,911,944,967]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">serpentina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(serpentine) in reference to the contorted leafmine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
